        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nThank you for this cleanup.\n\nWhile it should be benign and a no-op, making these changes IS a code change. You should add copyright lines for your company to each changed file.\n\n\n\nThere is a JIRA ticket I'd definitely like you to write that your code changes pointed out to me, and that's on the database execute calls. Please respond to the comment with the JIRA ticket number.\n\n\n\nYou might want to consider making the change to remove extraneous parentheses on if and while statements, such as changing\n\nif (envPytest == 'test'):\n\nto\n\nif envPytest == 'test':\n\nIf you'd rather do that in a separate submission, I understand. If so, please add the JIRA ticket in the comments as well.",
